---
alwaysApply: true
---
Follow these rules when developing:

1. Stack:
   - (not described jet)

2. When changing existing classes, try to use file renaming (`git mv`)
   instead of creating new ones and deleting old ones where possible.

3. When rename class, look for data types of properties, parameters and variables.
   If their names match old class name then rename them too.

4. Write all comments in code and everything that is output to logs or console in English.

5. Nether use comments like `@phpstan-ignore-next-line` which suppress issues detected by PHPStan.

6. Do not add more than ONE blank line in a row to any file (.php, .yaml, .md and so on):
   - Maximum 1 blank line to separate logical blocks.
   - Maximum 1 blank line at the end of the file.

7. Do not create new documentation files without an explicit request.

8. Project runs in Docker containers configured in `compose.yaml`.
   To execute shell scripts, add prefix `docker compose exec php-cli ` to them.

9. When editing PHP classes, keep methods, properties, and constants ordered per
   `.cursor/rules/architecture-naming-and-sorting.mdc` (do not leave new members only at the end of the file
   if sort order requires another place).

10. After creating or updating *.php files, at the end of the work run these shell scripts:
   - PHP CS Fixer: `composer cs-fix -- --show-progress=none`
   - PHPStan: `composer phpstan`

11. Don't run tests, `cs-fix` and `phpstan` when only documentation is updated.

12. When you have to run tests then call shell script `composer test-all`
